formatDescription: FrameMD5 is incorporated by ffmpeg and is used to generate frame by frame checksums of each decoded audio and video frame within a media file. For each frame it provides a timestamp, size in bytes, and an MD5 checksum, which can be used to verify the integrity of the decoded data.
